comments.text: When something sometimes works and then not you should check the environment and the command output on stdout/sdterr. So I would note the available node.js version(s) and the command output every time you execute npm install also check the installed node packages frida-example-agent depends on.
I tried different node version, v14.15.0, v16.20.2,.v18.17.1, not work at all, and the repo only rely on frida-compile15.0.8 and frida-compile itself seems working fine
I found the same problem in frida-compile' issue , but it's not closed, I just want a local env that can work fine. What should I do?
